						<a class="post_more_title" href="https://lithub.com/motherhood-and-the-moon-on-liminal-states-of-change-and-uncertainty/">
				<h4 style="margin:0">Motherhood and the Moon: On Liminal States of Change and Uncertainty</h4>
			</a>
			The Sun sets. The Moon sets. But they are not gone. This is from a poem a friend once sent me by the Islamic poet Jalal al-Din...			
			</div>
		</div>
		
					<div class='htlad-LH_PP_ALB'></div>
		
	
